e-to-oily-skin/" target="_blank">Gillette UK</a> suggests that another factor that may worsen oily skin in men is stress. When you’re stressed, cortisol levels rise in the body and this causes more oil production. Simple lifestyle changes like a long walk on the weekend and a cup of chamomile tea before you go to sleep can make a big difference.<br><br>The other causes of oily skin in men could be:<br><br><b>DHT</b>&nbsp;– Hormone dihydrotestosterone (DHT) causes oily skin and male pattern baldness.<br><br><b>Genetics</b> – Oily skin runs in men much like high sugar levels and other medical conditions.<br><br><b>Exposure to UV rays</b> – The sun may wreak havoc on men’s skin and increase oil production. Too much exposure to the sun may cause your skin to become wrinkled and leathery.<br><br><b>Weather changes</b> – Sudden changes in the weather can cause the skin to expand and contract, resulting in excess oil production.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-18_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-20_">How do you prevent oily skin?</span></h2><p class="sc-fmBCVi laenLa pf-21_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-23_">Start from the inside out. Add some fenugreek seeds to a glass of water at night, let it soak the entire night. In the morning, drink the water on an empty stomach. Do it religiously for glowing skin and hair.<br><br>Products containing the following ingredients may prevent oily skin;<br><br><b>Salicylic acid:&nbsp;</b>Helps alleviate acne scarring whilst keeping pores clean. <br><br>Salicylic acid is a beta hydroxy acid (BHA) that helps exfoliate and allows dry, dead skin cells to microscopically flake off the skin. Because it is oil soluble, it can penetrate through oil glands in the skin to unclog pores as well as fight inflammation. If you’re looking for the best way to prevent acne and combat ingrown hairs after shaving, salicylic acid is the product for you!<br><br><b>Niacinamide &amp; Retinol:&nbsp;</b>Help reduce appearance of large pores. <br><br>Niacinamide is an essential water-soluble vitamin and a form of vitamin B3 or niacin. It is also known as nicotinamide. As an essential vitamin, people must get niacinamide from their diet as the body cannot produce it. Many skin care products now contain niacinamide to deliver some of its benefits to the skin.<br><br>Retinol is an over-the-counter (OTC) form of retinoid, a vitamin A derivative. Vitamin A is another essential vitamin that people must get from their diets. It plays a vital role in immunity, eye health, and skin health.<br><br><b>Hyaluronic acid:&nbsp;</b>Helps balance moisture levels in the skin.<br><br>Hyaluronic acid is a natural substance found in the fluids in the eyes and joints. It acts as a cushion and lubricant in the joints and other tissues. Different forms of hyaluronic acid are used for cosmetic purposes. Hyaluronic acid might also affect the way the body responds to injury and helps decrease swelling. Your skin contains about half of the hyaluronic acid in your body. Hyaluronic acid binds to water molecules, which helps keep the skin hydrated and supple. Levels of hyaluronic acid in the skin significantly decrease as people age, which can lead to dehydrated skin and wrinkles.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-24_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-26_">Best Cleansers for Oily Skin</span></h2><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-94_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-lg:30px" data-href="/products/buy-aesop-amazing-face-cleanser" data-target="_blank" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-95_"><div data-product-id="6980763189400" data-pf-type="ProductMedia" class="sc-fivaXQ klojpP pf-96_">
